   Voter Information


   Carolyn A. Jackson Photo Thank you for taking the time to visit the web
   site for the Hamilton County Election Commission. The office of the
   Election Commission is responsible for the planning, conducting and
   administration of all municipal, county, state and federal elections
   held in Hamilton County. It is also responsible for maintaining the
   voter registration records of more than 170,000 Hamilton County
   citizens.

   The Hamilton County Election Commission consists of five appointed
   members:
     * Tyrone L. Waller, Chairman
     * Michael S. Walden, Secretary
     * Wesley Kliner, Commissioner
     * Linda Johnson, Commissioner

   The Election Commission office has a staff of 12 under the
   administration of Carolyn A. Jackson.

   Our responsibilities include verifying the qualifying papers of
   prospective candidates, overseeing the filing of campaign financial
   disclosure documents, ballot design, conducting early voting and
   absentee by mail voting for all elections, poll worker training and
   conducting election day voting and election result tabulation.

                                       I hope to see you all at the polls!
                                                       Carolyn A. Jackson,
                                                Administrator of Elections

